COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 408, L.D. 640
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment requires the court to inform all prospective parties to a court judgment
33 or decree that a 5% fee will be assessed on all accrued interest whenever a court receives
44 any money to be held by the court. The amendment also clarifies that the nonprevailing
55 party shall pay a 5% fee, capped at $1,000, based on all accrued interest while the court
66 held the money.
